Expense Tracker API

A RESTful backend API built with Node.js, Express, and MongoDB for managing personal finances. It features secure user authentication using JSON Web Tokens (JWT) and full CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) functionality for tracking expenses.

🚀 Tech Stack

Runtime: Node.js

Framework: Express.js

Database: MongoDB & Mongoose

Authentication: JSON Web Tokens (JWT)

Security: bcryptjs (Password Hashing)

📁 Project Structure

├── config/
│   └── mongodb.js           # Database connection setup
├── controllers/
│   ├── authController.js    # Registration and login logic
│   └── expenseController.js # Expense CRUD logic
├── middleware/
│   └── authMiddleware.js    # JWT verification and route protection
├── models/
│   ├── Expense.js           # Expense database schema
│   └── userSchema.js        # User database schema
├── routes/
│   ├── authRoutes.js        # /api/auth endpoints
│   └── expenseRoutes.js     # /api/expenses endpoints
├── server.js                # Main application entry point
└── package.json


🛠️ Installation & Setup

Clone the repository (or download the source code).

Install dependencies:

npm install


Set up Environment Variables:
Create a .env file in the root of your project and add the following variables:

PORT=8000
MONGO_URL=your_mongodb_connection_string_here
JWT_SECRET=your_super_secret_jwt_key


Run the server:

For development (using nodemon):

npm run dev


For production:

npm start


(The server should start on http://localhost:8000)

📡 API Endpoints

Authentication (/api/auth)

1. Register a new user

Method: POST

URL: /api/auth/register

Body (JSON):

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}


2. Log in

Method: POST

URL: /api/auth/login

Body (JSON):

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "password": "password123"
}


Response: Returns a JWT token. Save this token to use the protected expense routes.

Expenses (/api/expenses)

⚠️ Note: All expense routes are protected. You must include the JWT token in the request headers: Authorization: Bearer <your_token>

1. Get all expenses (for logged-in user)

Method: GET

URL: /api/expenses

2. Add a new expense

Method: POST

URL: /api/expenses

Body (JSON):

{
  "title": "New Mechanical Keyboard",
  "amount": 120.50,
  "category": "Electronics"
}


3. Update an expense

Method: PUT

URL: /api/expenses/:id (Replace :id with the actual expense ID)

Body (JSON):

{
  "amount": 105.00
}


4. Delete an expense

Method: DELETE

URL: /api/expenses/:id (Replace :id with the actual expense ID)

🛡️ Security Features

Password Hashing: User passwords are encrypted using bcryptjs before being saved to the database.

Route Protection: Custom middleware ensures that only authenticated users with a valid JWT can access, create, or modify expense data.

Data Ownership: Users can only view, edit, and delete their own expenses, linked securely via their unique User ID.